<HEADLINE> Iran Releases 275 Iraqi POWs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Thursday released 275
Iraqi prisoners of war (POWs) and they arrived at the
al-Muntheriya border checking point in the evening, the Iraqi News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Fahmi Al-Qaisi, an Iraqi official in charge of the POWs issue,
said in a statement that the Iranian side has informed Iraq of
their readiness to release a new batch of Iraqi POWs.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that Iran will release the remaining 11,000
Iraqi POWs registered in the International Red Crescent and
provide information about 4,000 Iraqis missing in actions (MIAs).
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi side has received an invitation to visit Tehran in
November to continue negotiations on the issue of POWs and MIAs,
said the official.
</P>
<P>
Iran announced earlier this week that Iran has freed 55,438
Iraqi POWs so far, while Iraq has freed 39,417 Iranian POWs. Iran
said there are still 2,806 Iranian POWs being kept in Iraqi
prisons.
</P>
<P>
Iraq and Iran fought an eight-year bloody war from 1980-88, in
which some one million people from both sides were killed or
injured.
</P>
<P>
The issue of POWs has become one of the major obstacles that
impedes improvement of relations between the two countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
