<HEADLINE> NATO Establishes New Headquarters in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) inaugurated Thursday the installation of the
new headquarters of Southwest Europe at Rematares, Madrid.
</P>
<P>
According to NATO, the instalment of the new headquarters
implies the disappearance of the one in Gibraltar, which was
manned by British soldiers.
</P>
<P>
NATO named Spanish General Lieutenant Juan Narro Romero head of
the new Southwest subregional headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar and NATO General
Secretary Javier Solana attended the inauguration ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Solana considered it necessary for Europe to have a role
comparable in security and defense to that of its economic and
political weight in the world.
</P>
<P>
"We have gone from an alliance exclusively designed to assure
collective defense of its members, to one determined in achieving
a more stable Europe, prosperous and peaceful," said Solana.
</P>
</TEXT>
