<HEADLINE> Zambia Moves to Control Foot-Mouth Disease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has banned all
livestock movement and hunting licence issuance from the concerned
areas to stop foot- mouth disease from spreading to other areas of
the country.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture, Food and Livestock imposed the ban
here Thursday, which applies to the areas of Livingstone,
Kazungula and Kalomo districts in the Southern Province and
Sesheke and Kalomo districts in the Western Province.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a statement that movement of all domestic
and game animals and animal products within, into and out of these
areas is prohibited.
</P>
<P>
It also said that the veterinary officers and wildlife officers
in the affected areas will take any other measures to control the
disease.
</P>
<P>
All cattle owners will be required to present their animals for
 vaccinations when asked by veterinary officers, said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
The ministry advised in the statement all those who obtained
hunting licences before the ban to report to national parks and
wildlife service offices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
