<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Causes At Least 6 Dead in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 30 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring
7.4 degree on the Richter scale jolted Mexico on Thursday, leaving
at least six dead and numerous buildings damaged.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was in the Pacific coast states of Oaxaca and
Guerrero, some 350 kilometers south of Mexico City. People in the
capital felt the tremor strong and run out from their buildings
when the tremor occurred at 11:35 local time.
</P>
<P>
At least 5 people were killed in Oaxaca, capital of the state
of the same name. One man was killed by a fallen concrete canopy.
The city is a popular tourist destination.
</P>
<P>
The quake was felt as far south as Chiapas state, 800
kilometers southeast of Mexico City. It destroyed some cars in
Pueble, some 80 kilometers southeast from Mexico City.
</P>
<P>
Mexico City, one of the world's largest cities with nearly 20
million residents in the metro area, suffered a major quake on
September 19, 1985, when an 8.1-magnitude quake struck, killing at
least 9,500 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
