<HEADLINE> Saddam Receives Letter From Yeltsin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi President Saddam
Hussein on Thursday received a letter from his Russian
counterpart Boris Yeltsin in which Yeltsin said Russia would work
for the lifting of the United Nations sanctions on Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's letter was conveyed to Saddam during his meeting
with visiting Russian Minister of Fuel and Energy Victor
Kalyuzhni, who arrived here Tuesday evening to attend the third
session of the Iraqi-Russian Economic, Trade and Technical Joint
Committee.
</P>
<P>
In his letter, Yeltsin appreciated the bilateral relations
between Russia and Iraq and expressed Russia's desire to improve
the relations with Iraq in all fields, the Iraqi News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Saddam said Iraq is committed to and will work
for enhancing the historical relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi president said that to consolidate the Iraqi-Russian
relations will enable the two countries to "confront threats from
other parties which aim at harming the legitimate interests of
Iraq and the Arab nation as well as Russia's role in the region."
</P>
<P>
Saddam expressed Iraq's desire to continue its cooperation
with Russia at all levels to achieve the common interests of two
friendly countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
