<HEADLINE> Rockefeller Foundation Opens Regional Office In </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The regional office of the
Rockefeller Foundation was opened here on Thursday to consolidate
its poverty- alleviation programs in southern Africa.
</P>
<P>
Gordon Conway, president of the Rockefeller Foundation, said at
the opening ceremony that the foundation is committed to bettering
the lives of the poor throughout the world.
</P>
<P>
It aims at improving food security for the poor, advancing
their health care, supporting diverse creative expression and
enhancing the participation of the poor in a democratic society,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Conway emphasized the need of gender equality for the full
development of a society.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that countries cannot experience growth either
economically or socially until men and women develop at the same
level," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwean Lands and Agriculture Minister Kumbirai Kangai said
the establishment of a regional office in its capital signaled
the foundation's commitment to expanding its activities not only
in Zimbabwe but also throughout the region.
</P>
<P>
He said the foundation had a world acclaimed reputation for its
 commitment to sustaining the lives of the disadvantaged.
</P>
<P>
Its focus on agriculture in Africa is to help government and
non- governmental institutions develop technologies, institutions
and policies that improve the well being of the marginalized small
holder agricultural sector, he said.
</P>
<P>
The foundation's regional program has seen rural development
projects being implemented in Botswana, Swaziland, Lesotho,
Malawi, South Africa and Zimbabwe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
