<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Concerned over Violence in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Russia on Thursday expressed
serious concern over the ongoing violence in Kosovo fueled by
ethnic tensions in the Yugoslav province.
</P>
<P>
Two people were killed and 41 wounded in a terrorist attack in
Bresje on Tuesday. Most of the victims were Serbs, Russian Foreign
Ministry Spokesman Vladimir Rakhmanin said.
</P>
<P>
"Despite the precise terms of the U.N. Security Council,
violence, civilians' murders, arsons and looting continue in the
territory," the Interfax news agency quoted Rakhmanin as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Albanian extremists challenge the international community and
grossly violate resolution No. 1244 of the U.N. Security Council,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
This attack "proves that although the disarmament of the Kosovo
Liberation Army ended on September 19, weapons were concealed,"
Rakhmanin said.
</P>
<P>
"The Bresje events must be investigated efficiently and
impartially and the culprits punished," the spokesman said.
</P>
</TEXT>
