<HEADLINE> Palestinian Opposition Leader Returns to West Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- A senior leader of a major PLO
faction returned to the West Bank town of Jericho Thursday through
the Makramah Checkpoint on the Jordan River from Amman.
</P>
<P>
Mustafa Zibri, Deputy Secretary General of the Popular Front
for the Liberation of Palestine (PFLP) was greeted by Palestinian
Cabinet Secretary Tayeb Abdel Rahim and Minister of Civil Affair
Jamil Tarif as well as other PNA and PFLP supporters.
</P>
<P>
Abdel Rahim described Mustafa's return to the West Bank as a
symbol of unity of the Palestinian people in the final status
talks with Israel, the Voice of Palestine radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Mustafa expressed pleasure about his homecoming and
said he is looking forward to the return of all the Palestinian
refugees to their homes.
</P>
<P>
"My return shows the desire of the PFLP to shoulder the
responsibility with the Palestinian people in peace making,"
Mustafa said.
</P>
<P>
Two days ago, the PFLP held a second round of talks with the
Fatah Movement, the mainstay of the Palestine Liberation
Organization (PLO), in Amman.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Secretary General of the Democratic Front for the
Liberation of Palestine (DFLP) Nayef Hawatmeh told Israel Radio
that he has no knowledge of any application by the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) to Israel on his return to the self-rule
areas.
</P>
<P>
Real peace should be based on the U.N. Security Council
Resolution No.194 which provides for the right of the Palestinian
people to self-determination, Hawatmeh said.
</P>
<P>
On the possibility of DFLP's involvement in the final status
talks, he said it depends on the results of the consultations by
the DFLP-Fatah joint committee that was formed in Cairo early
August.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak was quoted by
Israel Radio as saying that his government is studying a PNA
proposal to allow Hawatmeh back to the West Bank with a view to
strengthening the pro-peace camp. 
</P>
