<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Holds Seminar on Environment Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- A two-day seminar on
problem analysis and synthesis on conservation and sustainable use
of biodiversity in the Eastern Rift Valley lakes opened here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Opening the workshop, General Manager of Environmental
Protection Authority Tewolde G/Egziabher said that the
conservation of biodiversity in the rift valley lakes region
should be given due attention as the area is more vulnerable to
ecosystem degradation and genetic erosion today than ever before.
</P>
<P>
The lakes in the region had also manifested declining water
levels and depletion in biological resources as a result of
environmental degradation, he said.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is expected to map out strategies and action plans
for conservation and sustainable utilization of resources in the
rift valley lakes, according to organizers of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian environmental experts recently urged the
government departments concerned to beef up efforts to protect
worsening environment.
</P>
<P>
Experts have warned that some parts of Ethiopia is being
endangered of desertification which in turn will aggravate soil
erosion and bring about degradation upon the productive lands.
</P>
