<HEADLINE> Jordanian PM: Jerusalem Should Be Capital of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Prime Minister Raouf
al-Rawabdeh said Thursday his kingdom stands for the establishment
of an independent Palestinian state with Jerusalem as its capital.
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed the Jordanian position when meeting with a
delegation of the British Royal College for Defense Studies
headed by Major General Biji Goudard, Jordan's official news
agency Petra said.
</P>
<P>
Rawabdeh said Jerusalem is part of the Palestinian territory
occupied by Israel during the 1967 Mideast war, and Jordan
supports the Palestinians to restore their rights and to set up an
independent state with the holy city as its capital.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will safeguard the rights of 1.3 million
Palestinian refugees in the kingdom to either return to their
homeland or demand for compensation.
</P>
<P>
Jordan has been a firm supporter and broker in the peace
process between Israel and the Palestinians after it signed a
peace treaty with the Jewish state in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Rawabdeh said Jordan is trying to keep friendly relations with
all countries based on dialogue, respect and mutual trust. 
</P>
