<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Marks International Day of Older Persons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- An all-day event is
organized at the U.N. headquarters in New York Thursday to
celebrate the International Day of Older Persons 1999, which falls
on September 30.
</P>
<P>
The event is organized by the Non-Governmental Organization
(NGO) Committee on Ageing in collaboration with the United Nations
Program on Ageing and the United Nations Department of Public
Information.
</P>
<P>
The growing needs of the world's ageing population will be the
focus of the event, during which Ambassador Julia T. Alvarez,
alternative representative of the Dominican Mission to the United
Nations, Aurelio Fernandez, counsellor for social affairs in the
Spanish Mission to the United Nations, will receive awards for
their tireless efforts in promoting the International Year of
Older Persons 1999.
</P>
<P>
Gillian Sorensen, U.N. assistant secretary-general for external
relations, will read the message of the U.N. secretary-general,
Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
Celebrated since 1992, this day has galvanized attention on
the issues facing the ageing populations, including poverty,
health care, and social isolation.
</P>
<P>
Often escaping attention as the world is facing the largest
generation of youth in history, more people are living longer than
ever before, yet in many countries, both developing and developed,
services for the elderly are limited.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
