<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0035 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU in Collision With U.S. on WTO Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) is
on a collision course with the United States since it insists on a
comprehensive settlement in a new round of global trade talks to
be launched at the end of November in Seattle, a newly published
EU report said.
</P>
<P>
Within the World Trade Organization (WTO), EU drafts of the
final Seattle declaration are already circulating, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The document drafted by Finland, which is holding current EU
presidency, "lays more emphasis on improving coherence on trade,
monetary and financial issues through cooperation between the WTO
and other international organizations from the International
Monetary Fund to the United Nations Conference on Trade and
Development."
</P>
<P>
But the document "puts the EU on a collision course with the
United States".
</P>
<P>
While the EU talks of a "single undertaking" to ensure the
priorities of WTO members are given equal treatment over the
planned three years of negotiations, Washington is pushing for an
"early harvest" approach whereby issues which can be resolved
swiftly will not be held up by other more complex talks, the
report pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Actually, the EU-U.S. dispute goes to the heart of the trade
negotiation process, according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
