<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Tests Surface to Air Missile Akash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 30 (Xinhua) -- India Thursday successfully
tested its multi-target surface-to-air missile Akash with a range
of 25 km from the Interim Test Range (ITR) at Chandipur of east
India's Orissa state, defense sources said.
</P>
<P>
Akash hit Nishant, a pilotless training aircraft (PTA) flown
earlier from the ITR, with desired accuracy, according to PTI.
</P>
<P>
The test was exclusively meant to measure the timing and range
of Akash, compared to Patriot missiles, and also its ability to
hit a moving object in different range.
</P>
<P>
Sources said the data collected from Thursday's experiment
would be analyzed and, if necessary, further tests would be
conducted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
