<HEADLINE> Sino-Ugandan Relations Hailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Amama Mbabazi , Ugandan state
minister for Regional Cooperation, Thursday spoke highly of the
existing Sino- Ugandan relations.
</P>
<P>
He described such relationship as smooth, adding that there are
 "bright prospects" for the growth of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Mbabazi made the remarks here Thursday evening at a grand
function hosted by the Chinese Embassy to Uganda to mark the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
He said: "Uganda and China enjoy good relations, especially
since the ruling National Resistance Movement came to power in
1986, Uganda has learnt a lot from China's experience in
developing its economy."
</P>
<P>
Mbabazi called for further strengthening of bilateral relations
 although the two countries have already had cooperation covering
a wide range of areas such as economy , trade and culture which
has gained momentum in recent years.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Ugandan government has attached great
importance to its relations with China. The exchange of visits by
high-ranking officials from both sides become more frequent than
ever. All these point to the bright prospects of bilateral ties,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Uganda Zhang Xujiang briefed more than
500 guests present at the function on China's recent economic
achievements and the country's foreign policies.
</P>
<P>
The unprecedented economic achievements that China has made
indicate that its leadership has chosen the right political system
and the right economic measures to recover the nation both
economically and politically, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
