<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Envoy Assumes Security Council Presidency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Sergei Lavrov, the
Russian permanent representative to the United Nations, Friday
took over the presidency of the 15-nation United Nations Security
Council for the month of October.
</P>
<P>
Lavrov succeeds Arnold Peter van Walsum, the Dutch permanent
representative to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council, which has 5 permanent members and 10
non-permanent members, rotates presidency every month according to
the English alphabetical order of the 15 countries.
</P>
<P>
Russia is one of the five permanent members of the Council with
veto powers, along with China, France, the United Kingdom and the
United States.
</P>
<P>
The issues of East Timor and Iraq are expected to be on the
agenda of the Security Council in October.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council is also expected to consider a proposal by
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan to send 6,000 peacekeepers to
Sierra Leone to promote the peace process in the West African
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
