<HEADLINE> Joint GCC Marine Drills Due in Qatar Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Naval forces from the Gulf
Cooperation Council (GCC) states will hold a two-week exercise
code-named "Solidarity Six" in Qatar on Saturday, a Qatari
military official said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The three-phase drills were aimed at rehearsing joint
operations in repulsing foreign aggressions, testing the command
and control centers as well as the communication systems of the
GCC air forces, training director of the games Said Al-Abdullah
was quoted by Kuwait News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
The GCC joint marine drills, which were first launched in
1984, are held every two years in a GCC state.
</P>
<P>
The GCC states usually hold joint war games with major Western
powers with which they have signed defense cooperation agreements.
</P>
<P>
The GCC, a regional political and economic alliance established
in 1981, comprises Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia and
the United Arab Emirates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
