<HEADLINE> Tajikistan Proposes Year of Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Land-locked Tajikistan
proposed Friday that the United Nations declare the year 2003 as
International Year of Water in view of worsening situation with
clean water.
</P>
<P>
President Emomali Rakhmonov warned that water and other
challenges now facing the world "are directly linked to problems
of security in the context of inter-independence".
</P>
<P>
Half of the global population lives in unsanitary conditions as
a result of water pollution, he told the 54th Session of the U.N.
General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
For the same reason, more than five million people die every
year and over three billion become ill, he said.
</P>
<P>
"With the population growth a likelihood of water wars
between states for fresh-water sources is becoming ever more
real", the President predicted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
