<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WHO, Togo to Hold Meeting on Tobacco Control in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The Regional Office for Africa of
the World Health Organization (WHO) and the Togolese government
are scheduled to hold an international meeting on tobacco control
on October 6-8 at Lome, Togo.
</P>
<P>
For the first time in the African region, WHO will bring
together representatives of 15 African countries to consider an
appropriate strategy to counter the advertising offensive by the
tobacco industry, according to a WHO press release.
</P>
<P>
The main objectives of the meeting will also include the
strengthening of political commitment of parliamentarians in the
African region to a draft Initiative for a Tobacco-free World and
to promoting the WHO Framework Agreement on Tobacco Control.
</P>
<P>
The African region is increasingly targeted by the tobacco
industry because of the decline in the market of developed
countries, WHO said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
