<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0064 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Big Fireworks Display For PRC Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Beijing celebrated the 50th
anniversary of the People's Republic of China with a spectacular
40-minute fireworks display this evening that lit up much of the
city.
</P>
<P>
The fireworks were mainly set off at sites around Tian'anmen
Square in the city center, where a National Day soiree for some
100,000 people was held, but there were 10 other sites around the
city for people who didn't have access to the square.
</P>
<P>
Each time new fireworks burst over Tian'anmen, cheers erupted
from the crowd of people converged on the square. Luo Zhihong, a
student at Beijing Polytechnic University who was taking part in
the dance shows on the square, said, "I shall never forget this
evening."
</P>
<P>
Zhang Tieshan, a member of the preparatory committee for the
event, said that some 200 kinds of fireworks, many of them
recently developed, were used and had impressive and meaningful
names like "Ode to the Motherland," "Star of Macao" and "Dawn of
the New Century."
</P>
<P>
Xue Juntang, a civil servant from the city's Chongwen District,
said that this was the first time he watched a fireworks display
on Tian'anmen Square and that he felt "really great."
</P>
<P>
In a residential compound a block away from Tian'anmen, a
retired teacher and his family stood quietly in the courtyard,
gazing at the beautiful patterns unfolding in the sky, said that
it was the most beautiful and touching scene he had ever seen.
</P>
<P>
The fireworks lit up the Monument to the People's Heroes in the
center of Tian'anmen Square, which was built 41 years ago to honor
those who gave their lives for a new, robust China.
</P>
<P>
The fireworks also illuminated the Macao Countdown Clock on the
east side of Tian'anmen Square, which was put there to greet the
return of Macao to the motherland in December of this year.
</P>
<P>
An old man at the square said that, in the past 50 years, since
the founding of new China, the Chinese have realized their 5,000-
year dream of prosperity and dignity.
</P>
<P>
At 10 p.m., the final burst of fireworks over Tian'anmen Square
came, and the 100,000 people on the square started singing
simultaneously the song "Singing in Praise of the Motherland."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
