<HEADLINE> Expressway In Northwest China Opens To Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A 78.2-km-long expressway in
northwest China's Shaanxi Province was opened today, dramatically
improving local traffic conditions.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the expressway, which runs from the city of
Weinan westward to Tongguan, was begun in April 1997 and was
built at a cost of 1.41 billion yuan. This includes 63.7 million
US dollars of loans from the World Bank (WB).
</P>
<P>
The new road will be connected with other expressways in the
province, and is expected to aid local economic growth by
providing more convenient traffic links with neighboring provinces.
</P>
</TEXT>
