<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Launches Action Plan for Senior citizens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Friday launched
the National Senior Citizens' Action Plan focusing on health care,
housing, social and recreational facilities for the old folks.
</P>
<P>
The plan which covered more than 60 programs including
development and education programs for senior citizens was the
result of the cooperation of various sectors, National Unity and
Social Development Minister Zaleha Ismail said.
</P>
<P>
"The government is serious in taking care of the old folk's
welfare as well as to improve their potential," the minister said
after the launch of the Senior Citizens Day 1999 celebration here
by the country's Supreme Head of State Sultan Salahuddin Abdul
Aziz Shah.
</P>
<P>
The old folk population is expected to increase by 11 percent
by the year 2020 from the present 1.2 million senior citizens out
of the country's 22 million population.
</P>
<P>
The government plans to set up the Senior Citizens Foundation
aimed to improve the standard of living of the group through
financial contributions, she said.
</P>
<P>
The task of planning for the group's future should not be
shouldered by the government alone, the minister said, adding the
cooperation of all parties is needed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
