<HEADLINE> Gold, Silver Down in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Gold prices reacted down
sharply on the bullion market Friday in Mumbai (Bombay) due to
fall in the international prices.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold, after a positive start at 4,650 rupees (108.14
U.S. dollars) per ten gram, turned weak towards the fag end to
close at 4,550 rupees (105.81 U.S. dollars), showing a big fall of
80 rupees (1.86 U.S. dollars) over the last close of 4,630 rupees
(107.67 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
22-carat gold was nominally quoted sharply lower at 4,210
rupees (97.91 U.S. dollars) per ten gram from Thursday's close of
4,280 rupees (99.53 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ready silver (.999 fineness) opened firm at 8,490
rupees (197.44 U.S. dollars) from 8,485 rupees (197.32 U.S.
dollars) previously.
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) declined by 50 rupees (1.16 U.S.
dollars) to 8,290 rupees (192.79 U.S. dollars) per kg. from
Thursday's close of 8,340 rupees (193.95 U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
