<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Closes Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Karachi Stock Exchange (KSE)
index fell Friday fearing deterioration of law and order situation
in Pakistan, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 index closed 1.19 points, or 0.10 percent lower to
1198.10 against Thursday's 1199.29.
</P>
<P>
The total volume traded Friday stood at 163.291 million shares
against Thursday's 134.138 million shares.
</P>
<P>
"Despite positive perception market started on a bearish note
due to the news regarding sectarian killings in Karachi Friday in
which nine persons were killed," said Fasal Abbas, a dealer with
Ali Hussain Rajabali Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Of the 215 active issues, losers beat gainers 95 to 51 while 69
remained unchanged. 
</P>
