<HEADLINE> India Wins More Gold Medals in South Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Indian wrestlers won seven of
the eight gold medals here Friday and sharpshooters took four gold
medals to lead the medal tally at the South Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
India now has 88 gold, 48 silver and 22 bronze medals.
</P>
<P>
In the wrestling finals, gold medal winners included Kirpa
Shanker Patel (48-54 kilogram category), Manoj Kumar (58) Mukesh
Kumar (63), Sujit Mann (69), Pawan Kumar(76), Anuj Kumar (85) and
Shamber Singh (97).
</P>
<P>
Only Pakistan's Mohammad Basir broke the Indian monopoly to win
the gold in the over 97-kilogram category.
</P>
<P>
In shooting, Indians took four of the five gold medals and Sri
Lanka the other.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, India will play against Bangladesh and host Nepal
meets Maldives in the soccer semifinals. The soccer final is
scheduled for Monday.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 athletes from Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, Maldives,
Nepal, Sri Lanka and Pakistan are participating in 12 events in
the games that are being held in the Nepalese capital. 
</P>
