<HEADLINE> Phoenix and Dragon Dance at National Day Evening Gala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Folk artists from Chongqing
Municipality in southwest China staged a phoenix and dragon dance
at the National Day evening Gala held at Tian'anmen Square this
evening.
</P>
<P>
Two 15-meter-long colorful phoenixes, composed of scores of
Chongqing girls, now fluttered among peony shrubs and then played
with two dragons. The two phoenixes were competing with the
dragons in both grace and styles.
</P>
<P>
Dragon dance is a popular form of performance among Chinese in
all parts of the world. However, phoenix dance has never been
shown in any part of world before.
</P>
<P>
Phoenix, an important mythical animal in traditional Chinese
culture, is regarded as the "king of birds."
</P>
<P>
Wang Shengming, deputy chief of Tongliang County, said the
county played nine dragons and two phoenixes during the National
Day evening gala.
</P>
<P>
"We wish our motherland prosperity and its people a peaceful
life by performing the dragon and phoenix dance," Wang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
