<HEADLINE> Weather Forecast for National Day Accurate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The weather on China's National
Day today turned out to be the same as forecast, providing fine
conditions for a smooth anniversary celebration.
</P>
<P>
The weather forecast reported that it would be partly cloudy
today, clearing up later, which proved to be true.
</P>
<P>
The accuracy indicated that China's technological level in
weather forecast has improved greatly, according to local
meteorologists.
</P>
<P>
High-tech means in weather forecast had been used for an
accurate forecast for the National Day and a total of 300 experts
and technicians were called in to predict the National Day weather,
said Li Huang, deputy director of the China Meteorological
Administration.
</P>
<P>
It started to rain yesterday afternoon and the rain got heavier
in the evening, but the rain stopped around 4:00 this morning.
</P>
