<HEADLINE> Carnival Ending for National Day Soiree (More Added) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The third part of the National
Day soiree started with 60 kids in crimson short gowns running
into the performance area below the Tian'anmen Rostrum and
starting to practise the Chinese martial arts.
</P>
<P>
Beijing is holding an evening gala in Tian'anmen Square to mark
the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of
China.
</P>
<P>
Several replica of the world-famous terra-cotta soldiers moved
slowly into the center of the arena, which, along with the
vigorous and inspiring performance of the kids, symbolized the
history full of noble aspiration and daring and the pioneering
spirit of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
When the music changed to a sweet and tender waltz, 100 couples
of young dancers in evening dresses swirled into the performance
area, turning the granite-paved section of the Chang'an Avenue
before the Tian'anmen Rostrum into a simple yet romantic dance
pool.
</P>
<P>
A float in the shape of a peony flower bud smoothly sailed into
the arena in the company of 300 performers wearing distinct
costumes of China's all 56 ethnic groups. When the flower
blossomed, three singers representing China's old, middle-aged and
young singers showed up and jointly presented the theme song of
the soiree: Good Luck to You, Motherland.
</P>
<P>
Bright and colorful fireworks were set off to the sky over
Tiananmen Square for the last time tonight, while one same song,
Ode to the Motherland, sung by all 100,000 participants of the
soiree resounded through the whole area. The soiree ended amidst
thunderous cheers and applause and in an extremely jubilant
atmosphere. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
