<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tian'anmen Square Becomes Sea of Lights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- While the first part of the
National Day soiree was concluded with a 10-minute fireworks
display, a harp-shape float shining with colorful lights and
carrying performers in various costumes of Chinese folk operas
slowly slid across the Tiananmen Rostrum, launching the second
part of the soiree.
</P>
<P>
Today is the 50th birthday of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
What the performers sang were arias from the famous Peking
Opera, which is reputed as the most precious legacy of the Chinese
culture, as well as from other popular Chinese folk operas, such
as the Shaoxing Opera, Henan Opera and Huangmei (Anhui) Opera.
</P>
<P>
Dancing around the float were 100 students from the Chinese
Opera Academy dressed up as various characters in folk operas and
dozens of kids brandishing colorful lanterns in the shape of carps
and lotus.
</P>
<P>
The opera float was followed by a float carrying several young
pop singers, who were singing songs eulogizing China's great
achievements over the past two decades of reform and opening-up.
The float was surrounded by nearly 1,000 teenagers holding silver-
colored electronic lights and dancing in brisk paces.
</P>
<P>
The second part of the soiree reached its climax when two
golden dragon lanterns, each 54 meters in length, and two more
than 10-meter-long phoenix lanterns emerged below the Tian'anmen
Rostrum. These lanterns were from Tongliang County of Chongqing
Municipality, which enjoys a nationwide fame as "the hometown of
lanterns." There were also 160 young girls holding large "peony
flowers" and dancing around the dragons and phoenixes.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people regard dragon and phoenix as symbols of good
luck, and bill the peony as "king of all flowers" for its natural
grace and elegance.
</P>
<P>
All performers in the phoenix lantern dancing, which allegedly
was introduced in major celebration occasions for the first time,
were female amateurs from the Tongliang County.
</P>
<P>
Various traditional lanterns and lights of modern science and
technology, such as spotlights, searchlights and laser lights,
have turned the vast Tiananmen Square into a sea of colorful
lights tonight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
