<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Floats at PRC 50th Anniversary Evening Gala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Of the 94 floats used in today's
grand celebration marking the 50th anniversary of the founding of
the People's Republic of China (PRC), four were specially designed
for the evening gala.
</P>
<P>
The four floats are serving as bellwethers of the different
square formations, backgrounds for artistic performances, and the
stage for several famous entertainers.
</P>
<P>
Featuring master drummers, the phoenix, modernity, and the
peony, the four floats are shaped in different styles but all
fully highlight the festive mood and incorporate Chinese design
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The master drummers float is a major morale-booster in the
celebration, giving the evening gala an atmosphere filled with
excitement and high spirits when it emerges at the forefront.
</P>
<P>
A large drum is positioned at the highest point on the float,
as five master drummers, four of whom are women, play the drum to
earsplitting levels and lead the other drummers.
</P>
<P>
The phoenix float echoes the huge dragon float shown during the
daytime celebration, a harbinger of good luck.
</P>
<P>
The modern float spotlights the features of the modern era, as
it continues to glisten thanks to the application of high
technologies.
</P>
<P>
The blooming peonies are used in the peony float to symbolize
peace and stability for China and its people.
</P>
<P>
New materials and technologies involving acoustics, lighting,
and electronics are used in creating the floats.
</P>
<P>
The latest multicolored electronic neon lights were applied to
decorate the floats, and they take on different patterns in the
evening.
</P>
<P>
Colorful fire-proof materials were also used for the outfit of
the floats. The floats displayed in the grand celebration marking
the 50th anniversary of the founding of the PRC reflect the
overall development of new China's modern industries.
</P>
<P>
All the float drivers are specially trained and demonstrate
fine driving skills. They are required to drive the floats at a
speed in tandem with the moving performances. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
