<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tian'anmen Looks Brighter on National Day Evening </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Tian'anmen Square, in the center
of Beijing, became a sea of lights woven by beam lights of
searchlights and thousands of colored lights on the National Day
evening.
</P>
<P>
Four lights on poles of a height ranging from 29 meters to 35
meters have been installed on the nearly 450,000-square-meter
square. Each light is composed of 38 bulbs with 12 for long
distance illumination and 26 for close illumination.
</P>
<P>
Twenty newly-developed searchlights flank the Tian'anmen Square.
Thirty laser lights have been erected in front of the Memorial
Hall of Mao Zedong. All these lights are controlled by computers.
</P>
<P>
The Monument to the People's Heroes is encircled by hundreds of
reflector lights tonight. Workers have also increased the power of
lights decorating the outline of major buildings at the Tian'anmen
Square including the Great Hall of the People, Memorial Hall of
Mao Zedong, Museum of the Chinese Revolution, and Museum of
Chinese History. Eight 24-kilowatt beacons are added on the
Tian'anmen Rostrum.
</P>
<P>
The 315 trees lining the pavement on the eastern and western
sides of the Tiananmen Square have been decorated with numerous
colored lights. In addition, two floor lamps were recently erected
beside each tree to make them brighter at night.
</P>
<P>
Colorful "rainbow bridges" stride across the Chang'an Avenue at
Jianguomen and Fuxingmen. Neon light decorated on the "rainbow
bridges" glisten at night, adding festival atmosphere to the
National Day.
</P>
<P>
Numerous electric bulbs are hung on pines on both sides of
Xinhuamen, the main entrance of Zhongnanhai, the headquarters of
the Communist Party of China and the central government, to create
an effect of a star-studded sky.
</P>
<P>
Chinese lanterns can be seen at many parts at the Wangfujing
shopping center, Xidan Cultural Square and other revenues and
lanes this evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
