<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Extend EMS Service to More Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will start
international Express Mail Service (EMS) with seven more countries
by the end of this year, a high official of Bangladesh Postal
Department (BPD) said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The countries are Brunei, Belgium, Yemen, Uzbekistan, South
Africa, Lebanon and Syria.
</P>
<P>
With these countries, Bangladesh will operate the EMS with 52
countries and regions to send letters, business documents,
samples, merchandise up to a maximum of 20 kilograms on a quicker
way like other international courier service, the official was
quoted by BSS news agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh entered the EMS in July 1984 when it made an
arrangement with Britain for receiving inward data post items.
</P>
<P>
The BPD dispatched more than 100,000 articles to different
countries and regions and received almost an equal number of items
for delivery across the country last year, according to the BSS.
</P>
</TEXT>
