<HEADLINE> PRC Birthday Celebrated in Samoa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Ambassador to Samoa
Wang Xinyuan gave a reception in Apia, capital of Samoa, on the
evening of September 30 (local time), marking the 50th anniversary
of the founding of the People's Republic of China (PRC), it was
learned from the Chinese Embassy there.
</P>
<P>
Attending the reception, which was permeated with an warm
atmosphere of friendship, were Tuimalealiifano Va'alato Sualauvi
II and Mataia Visesio Eropa, both members of the Council of
Deputies of Samoa; Tuala Sale Tagaloa, acting prime minister and
foreign minister; Toleafoa Faafisi, speaker of the Parliament, and
other some 100 personalities from various circles.
</P>
<P>
In his toast at the reception, Ambassador Wang said China hopes
to further its friendly relations of cooperation with Samoa.
</P>
<P>
Acting Prime Minister Tuala said in his toast that both Samoa
and China have enjoyed close relations with each other since the
two countries forged their diplomatic ties in 1975.
</P>
<P>
He highly appreciated the assistance China has provided to his
country over the years and said his country will, as in the past,
stick to one China policy and recognize the PRC. 
</P>
