<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
made strong gains to end the week, buoyed by a number of positive
factors including diminished interest rate fears in the United
States.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index closed 31.8 points or 1.10
percent stronger at 2912.9, just off its intraday high of 2915.0.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index surged 54.6 points or 1.11 percent
higher to close at 4983.0 with strong gains in the banking sector,
while the all resources index finished up 14.1 points or 1.08
percent at 1316.4.
</P>
<P>
Trade on the local bourse was heavy, with national turnover
reaching 414.98 million valued at 1.01 billion Australian dollars
(667 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Rises outnumbered falls 618 to 524, with 366 stocks steady.
</P>
<P>
Among the banks, National Australia Bank surged 66.9 cents
ahead to 23.10 Australian dollars, Westpac added 12.7 cents at
9.58 Australian dollars and the ANZ managed a five cent gain to
10.30 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Commonwealth Bank gained 20 cents to 24.35 Australian
dollars, adding to Thursday's gains. 
</P>
