<HEADLINE> South Asian Dermatology Conference Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The first South Asian Regional
Conference on Dermatology (SARCD) began here Friday with the
participation of about 500 delegates from South Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
The main theme of the conference is "regional collaboration in
Dermatology, Venereology and Leprology (DVL)", said Dr. Anil Kumar
Jha, organizing secretary of SARCD, in his key notes address to
the conference.
</P>
<P>
He said that the conference is to emphasize the importance of
interaction and cooperation in DVL, both within the region and
also with the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from countries outside the region including the
United States, Japan, Switzerland, Poland and Britain are also
invited to the conference.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Jha said the first SARCD is one of the steps to achieve the
goal to "intensify and expand our advocacy" for the study of DVL
and get its due place and recognition at national and
international level.
</P>
<P>
Skin diseases, leprosy and sexually transmitted diseases are
prevalent in South Asia. Poverty, ignorance and lack of proper
hygiene are the main factors for the spread of most of the
communicable diseases in the region.
</P>
<P>
However, the study and treatment of the diseases has not been
given the attention it deserves in the region. 
</P>
