<HEADLINE> South Korea Suffered 31 Earthquakes This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-one earthquakes struck
South Korea in the first nine month of this year, a sharp rise
compared to the annual average of 17 cases in the past years.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen tremors were measured above five on the Richter scale,
according to South Korean Yonhap News.
</P>
<P>
The eastern part of the nation, consisting of Kangwon Province
and Kyongsang Province, was the most vulnerable to quakes. The two
provinces have recorded 19 quakes each since 1996, and Kangwon
suffered nine this year alone.
</P>
<P>
A total of 186 earthquakes has occurred in the country since
1978 when it started official records of tremors.
</P>
<P>
Yonhap News quoted experts as saying that a tremor of above 6
on the Richter scale may strike South Korea within the next 10
years. 
</P>
