that as negotiated with the local Waverley council in east Sydney,
the Olympic Coordination Authority (OCA) will provide 1 million
Australian dollars (about 650,000 U.S. dollars) to refurbish and
upgrade a pavilion at the world-famous Bondi beach.
</P>
<P>
Local residents complained about the proposal and one homeowner
took the OCA to court to try to have the stadium location changed.
The residents claim that the facility will ruin the beach for a
six-month period and should never have been considered for such a
popular area.
</P>
<P>
Construction will begin in early May, with a main court and
five practice courts also to be constructed.
</P>
<P>
Public access along the promenade in front of the pavilion will
be maintained for as long as possible but will be closed during
August and September 2000. 
