<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Half Million People Join National Day Celebrations in Beijing (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Half a million people from all
walks of life participated in today's parade in Beijing to
celebrate the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
The parade is the first panoramic presentation of New China's
founding and development.
</P>
<P>
A huge picture of the late Chinese leader Mao Zedong showed up
at the head of the civilian procession, while large pictures of
Deng Xiaoping, the late architect of China's reform and opening-up
policy, and Jiang Zemin, State President and General Secretary of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, appeared in
the National Day parades for the first time.
</P>
<P>
Today's civilian parade consisted of three parts illustrating
the three periods of the CPC-led revolution to overthrow the
reactionary Kuomintang regime and the birth and development of New
China.
</P>
<P>
The first part of the procession included 10 floats dipicting
the Long March, the War of Resistance against Japan, the
Liberation War against the Kuomintang regime, and the founding of
New China.
</P>
<P>
The first float carried a large picture showing Mao Zedong
declaring the founding of the People's Republic on October 1, 1949.
When it moved past the Tian'anmen Square the paraders shouted, "
Long live the motherland" and "Long live the Communist Party", to
the music of the song "There would be no New China with the
Communist Party".
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0157 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Half Million People Join National Day Celebrations in Beijing (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There were 40 floats in the second part of the parade
procession. A large picture showing Deng Xiaoping on the
Tian'anmen Rostrum moved in front, followed by other floats
illustrating China's achievements in the reform and opening-up
over the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
Industrial workers and farmers marched in front, followed by
scientists, teachers, students, artists, sportsmen,
representatives of private sectors, religious circles and
handicapped people.
</P>
<P>
The third part, which integrated 40 floats, showed the Chinese
people's determination to continue the cause of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics into the 21th century.
</P>
<P>
A float in front carrying Jiang Zemin's picture was flocked by
5,000 representatives of 56 ethnic groups in the country. I also
carried a model of the pamphlet of the report delivered by Jiang
at the 15th National Congress of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
It was followed by floats representing 31 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions as well as the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region, Macao and Taiwan. A countdown board
on the Macao float showed the date of Macao's return to the
motherland on December 20. On the float representing Taiwan
Province was a slogan "The Taiwan question cannot be put off
indefinitely".
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands children in five square formations symbolized
the future and hope of the country.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the parade, the words "peace and development"
appeared in the background.  
