<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Anniversary Parade Ushers in New Century (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Following the floats of portraits are farmers, fashion models,
ballet dancers, private entrepreneurs, and intellectuals. Although
their experiences have been so different during the past 50 years,
now they are marching together to the same goal of turning China
into a democratic, prosperous, and strong socialist country with a
high level of civilization.
</P>
<P>
Some touches of vivacity were added to the usually solemn
anniversary parade this year: cartoons of fruits and domestic
animals and poultry were used to show the joy and happiness of the
people for a better life; groups of children roller-skaters also
appeared in the parade.
</P>
<P>
A 1,200-member military band played the latest popular music on
the square, to accompany the marching of the paraders.
</P>
<P>
Viewers were busy posing for pictures, taking the marching
paraders as the backdrop.
</P>
<P>
Added to the spectacle of the parade was a group of local
floats, representing the 31 provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions, and Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan regions.
</P>
<P>
Perfect orderliness continues to be a prominent characteristic
of the anniversary parade, which is obviously seen from the
shouting of slogans, frequent changes of the background patterns
on the square and the perfect timing of the formations marching
across the square.
</P>
<P>
In their finery, university students whipped the flags
representing their schools energetically so that the leaders on
the Tian'anmen Rostrum could see their school names on the flags.
</P>
<P>
The leaders smiled and waved to the paraders now and then, who
cheered back with broad smiles and roaring shouts of slogans.
</P>
<P>
World champions also joined the civilian parade. "It is surely
different from attending the opening ceremony of Olympic Games,
but the feeling of pride is similar," said Deng Yaping, a famous
female world table tennis champion.
</P>
<P>
The grand celebrations were televised live by the China Central
Television (CCTV) and at least 26 overseas TV stations broadcast
live on the internet, attracting so many viewers that city streets
have become virtually deserted.
</P>
<P>
The whole country was immersed in a festive atmosphere as a
result of the celebrations.
</P>
<P>
"We can not imagine how the anniversary celebrations will be
like 50 years from now, but I'm definitely sure that China will
become much better by then," Liu Baoqin said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
