<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PRC 50th Anniversary Celebrated in Local Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The 50th anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic of China (PRC), which fell on
today, was grandly celebrated in Beijing, the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The great event is also marked nationwide in different ways.
</P>
<P>
In Changchun, capital of northeast China's Jilin Province and
birthplace of the country's auto industry, tens of thousands of
urban civilians braved the rains to attend parties and
performances staged at the cultural plaza in the city's downtown
area.
</P>
<P>
In Lhasa, capital of southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region,
the red five-star national flag was raised in front of the Potala
Place at eight a.m. with well over 3,000 people attending and
singing the national anthem.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region also held a special national
flag raising ceremony at the central square of Urumqi, the
regional capital, early this morning to mark the PRC 50th founding
anniversary, with 5,600 people from across the region attending.
</P>
<P>
The region also organized a range of other celebrating
activities including a garden party held at the city's
entertainment water world, and artistic performances in Urumqi's
seven major parks.
</P>
<P>
In Nanchang, capital of east China's Jiangxi Province and also
the birthplace of the Chinese army, tens of thousands of urban
residents woke up in early morning and flocked to the city's
August 1 Square to attend a special national flag hoisting
function held at seven a.m.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong Province's Zhuhai, the closest city to Macao,
organized a host of colorful activities to celebrate the 50th
anniversary of the birth of New China and the return of Macao to
the motherland which will fall on December 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
