<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing-Kowloon Railway Helping China's Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A model of the Beijing-Kowloon
Railway Line's Jiujiang Bridge can be seen on a communications
float in today's National Day parade.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Kowloon Railway Line has an important role in
increasing the pace of economic growth in coastal, central, and
eastern parts of the country and in increasing north-south traffic
and promoting prosperity and stability in Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
The 2,553-km railway line was the largest railway project ever
in China and cost 40 billion yuan. It is the country's third north-
south trunk line after the Beijing-Guangzhou and Beijing-Shanghai
lines, crossing 9 provinces and municipalities. The line went into
operation on September 1, 1996. It has greatly eased the strain on
north-south transport.
</P>
<P>
China plans to spend 100 billion yuan on industrial, energy,
and communication projects along the Beijing-Kowloon Railway Line
before the end of the century. They are based in 7 provinces and
cities along the line.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
