<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Telecoms Industry Growing Fast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- One of the floats in the
National Day procession symbolizes China's achievements in
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
China has had rapid development in its telecommunications
industry in the past 50 years. Industry revenues grew 35.7 percent
last year, nearly 5 times the growth of the nation's economy and
the fourth consecutive year the industry had growth above 30
percent.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Information Industry reported
telecommunications revenues, other than those of China Unicom, of
241.3 billion yuan in 1998.
</P>
<P>
China had more than 110 million phone customers by the end of
1998 and 24.98 million mobile phone customers. This was 28.34
million more than the figure of the previous year and equal to the
total for the 35 years from 1949 to 1994.
</P>
<P>
Spending on telecommunications infrastructure hit an all-time
high of 175.4 billion yuan last year and accounted for 6.1 percent
of China's total fixed assets spending.
</P>
<P>
The total length of fiber optic cables in China grew to 173,000
km. in 1998. The mobile phone sector was also a pillar of the
telecommunications industry. The number of customers is expected
to increase by 15 million this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
