<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- World 500cc championships
leader Alex Criville cracked a bone in his left wrist in opening
qualifying at Phillip Island on Friday.
</P>
<P>
But the Spaniard is still expected to ride in Sunday's
Australian GP.
</P>
<P>
Criville's bike slid from underneath him as he was sweeping
into the first corner in the last few minutes of the qualifying
session.
</P>
<P>
He quickly jumped to his feet but was taken by ambulance to
trackside medical staff, who later found the fracture.
</P>
<P>
Criville is anxious to protect his 46-point lead over American
Suzuki racer Kenny Roberts with four races or 100 points left in
the championship.
</P>
<P>
Roberts cranked up the pressure on Criville with the fastest
time by more than a second in Friday's opening qualifying, with
the Spaniard the ninth fastest, some 1.5 seconds down. 
