<HEADLINE> China Successful in 1st Test of High-Definition Telecasting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- China succeeded in its first
experimental high-definition telecasting today when the China
Central Television (CCTV) telecast live the grandeur parade at the
Tian'anmen Square to mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of
the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Over 20 places in the Beijing area were able to receive the
high-definition live telecasting today.
</P>
<P>
It is the first such test with the high-definition TV
technology in the country. Local experts hailed the successful
test as a new progress in China's development of TV technology,
and said the success is of profound importance to the development
of the country's broadcasting, television and information
industries.
</P>
<P>
But they noted that while industrial countries have made much
efforts in developing high-definition TV technology, China has
only made its first test in this field.
</P>
<P>
With the new technology, high-definition TV sets have a better
anti-interference ability and produce pictures (16 X 9 inches) in
size, and the picture may be as good as those produced by the 35-
mm wide film projectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
