<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Agricultural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- One colorful float with the
slogan: "Promote the modernization of agriculture" can be seen in
the National Day procession today.
</P>
<P>
The boat-shaped float represents China's agricultural march
toward modernization. Its four colors -- blue, green, white, and
gold -- symbolize aquatic agriculture, organic products, high-tech
farming, and good harvests, respectively.
</P>
<P>
China's agricultural sector has had steady growth over the past
50 years and China has created a miracle by feeding 22 percent of
the world's population on 10 percent of its arable land.
</P>
<P>
In those 50 years since the e founding of new China, it has
increased grain output from 100 million tons in 1949 to 490
million tons in 1998, with an average annual increase of 8 million
tons.
</P>
<P>
China's cotton output was 4.4 million tons in 1998 and China
ranks first in the world in cereal grain, cotton, peanut, rape-
seed, and fruit output.
</P>
<P>
Its annual pork, mutton, and beef output totaled 40 million
tons in 1997, a 12-fold increase from the early 1950s.
</P>
<P>
Its aquatic product output was up 8.5 percent to 39 million
tons last year and industry sources predict continued output
growth this year.
</P>
<P>
China planted 5.2 million ha. of trees last year to increase
the country's total forested area to 130 million ha. It is trying
to increase its forest coverage to 19 percent and its urban
vegetation to 35 percent by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
The average annual per capita net income of Chinese farmers
increased from 44 yuan in 1949 to 2,162 in 1998, a 48-fold
increase in 50 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Hold Grand National Day Soiree </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Some 100,000 people from all
ethnic groups across China will gather at Tian'anmen Square in
downtown Beijing this evening for a grand soiree marking the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Top Communist Party and state leaders of China are expected to
be present on the Tian'anmen Rostrum opposite to the square when
the soiree begins at 8:00 p.m., and enjoy a large entertainment
show staged on the section of the Chang'an Avenue (Avenue of
Eternal Peace) at the foot of the rostrum.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the soiree and entertainment show, which
takes "Good Luck to You, Motherland" as its theme and is scheduled
to last some two hours, will be workers, farmers, students,
government officials, representatives of various ethnic minorities
and people from the arts and sports circles. Representatives from
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, Macao and Taiwan will
also attend the soiree.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the soiree said that it would be an ideal
occasion for people of all ethnic groups across the country to
express their happy and joy on the birthday of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
"Happy crowds, marvelous singing and dancing, and colorful
floats and fireworks displays will turn the vast Tian'anmen Square
into an ocean of joy this evening," one organizer commented.
</P>
<P>
The square will be divided into nine sub-areas in which some 80,
000 people from all walks of life will stage a "very impressive"
group dance, he added.
</P>
<P>
According to one director of the entertainment show, which is
believed to be the most fascinating part of the National Day
soiree, the show will feature almost all best performing arts of
the Chinese nation, such as lion and dragon dancing, acrobatics,
Beijing opera, Yangge dancing and drum dances, and will run in
three parts with fireworks displays filling the intervals.
</P>
<P>
" A section of the Chang'an Avenue between the Tian'anmen
Square and the Rostrum will be the central performance zone," said
the director. "All performers will march through this section and
perform all the way."
</P>
<P>
Apart from the Tian'anmen Square, 10 other sites have been
selected across Beijing for fireworks displays in the course of
the National Day soiree. 
</P>
</TEXT>
