<HEADLINE> China Now Able To Produce More Advanced GSI Chips </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 1 (Xinhua)-- China's first production line of
8-inch 0.35-micron GSI (grand scale integration) chips was
recently completed after 18 months of construction work at
Shanghai Huahong NEC Electronics Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
It has a monthly output of 5,000 chips and that is scheduled to
rise to 10,000 by the end of this year and 20,000 by early next
year.
</P>
<P>
The high-tech venture is backed by Shanghai Huahong (Group) Co.,
Ltd. and Japan's NEC and was built in the Pudong area of Shanghai
in 1997. Its main products are a 64-MB SDRAM (synchronous dynamic
random access memory) and circuits. 
</P>
