<HEADLINE> 62 of 500 Fortune Global Companies Invest Money in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A total of 62 of 500 fortune
global companies have chosen Tianjin to develop their business in
China, according to information from the just-concluded fortune
global forum in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Li Shenglin, mayor of Tianjin, said the total contracted
foreign investment has hit 3.8 billion U.S. dollars. Giant
companies like General Motors, Motorola, Shell, Siemens and Toyota
have invested heavily in the northern city.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, 70 percent of the 62 companies have made
profits because of the favorable environment of Tianjin. Motorola
(China) Electronics Co., Ltd., for instance, made profits of 2.08
billion yuan (about 251 million U.S. dollars) in the first eight
months of 1999, 53 percent up on the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The achievements have boosted the confidence of foreign
investors, many of whom have decided to reinvest in Tianjin.
</P>
</TEXT>
