<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Military Parade Unveils New Arms of Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Military analysts say that such additions showed the
development of China's armed forces and the strengthening of
China's military strength during the past five decades since the
founding of the People's Republic in 1949.
</P>
<P>
The marine corps, initiated in the early 1980s, are capable of
rapid land, air, on-the-sea and under-water deployment, experts
disclose.
</P>
<P>
The army reserve was set up at the proposal of Deng Xiaoping,
architect of China's reform and opening in 1986, when China
announced its decision to reduce one million of its People's
Liberation Army (PLA) servicemen. China pledged to cut another 500,
000 from its muster roll last year and the military reserve are
being beefed up.
</P>
<P>
The special police unit was formed in the early 1990s to
counter hijacking, terrorism and other violent crimes. It is a
specially-trained, specially-armed, quick-action task force
targeted at special missions.
</P>
<P>
China's ground forces established their first anti-aircraft
missile troops at the end of 1991. The new arm is capable of low-
altitude and super-low altitude air defense missions.
</P>
<P>
The air unit of the ground forces was formed in August, 1988
and are equipped with helicopter gunships.
</P>
<P>
The air unit of the navy was inaugurated in April 1953. It
plays an important role in the defense of territorial waters.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0211 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Sectors Urged to Beat Y2K Bug Deadline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Y2K Commission
Friday appealed to those concerned corporations and government
agencies to speed up the submission of their readiness disclosures
and beat the deadline.
</P>
<P>
In an interview here, Y2K Commission Executive Director Karim
Bangcola made the appeal in light of reports that only some 200
companies, including government agencies, have complied with the
Y2K requirements.
</P>
<P>
The commission is now closely monitoring the activities of
these companies, particularly the sensitive ones which might
create chaos in case a problem crops up in their computer systems
and disrupt the efficient service they provide to the public,
Bangcola said.
</P>
<P>
However, he said that the banking sector is already 100 percent
Y2K ready.
</P>
<P>
According to Bangcola, important government agencies, such as
the Government Service Insurance System (GSIS) and the Social
Security System (SSS), the Bureau of Internal Revenue (BIR,
Department of Finance, the Central Bank of the Philippines, are
also Y2K ready.
</P>
<P>
The official deadline for the Y2K compliance by some
corporations and government agencies was set on September 30,
while others have requested for extension up to the end of the
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
