<HEADLINE> 6 Pct of Bangladeshi Population Over 60 Years Old </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- More than 7.2 million people in
Bangladesh are above 60 years old, accounting for nearly 6 percent
of the country's population of 126 million, The Bangladesh
Observer reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The number of elderly people in the country would rise in the
future following the development of medical science and the rising
life expectancy, the report quoted speakers as saying on Thursday
at a discussion organized in observance of the International
Elderly Day which falls on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The average life expectancy in Bangladesh is 59 years at
present.
</P>
<P>
The child mortality rate has come down, and the number of
fertile couples is on the rise, they said.
</P>
<P>
In separate messages on the occasion of the Elderly Day,
President Shahabuddin Ahmed and Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina urged
the well-off people in the country and non-governmental
organizations to come up with programs for the aging society
alongside those of the government.
</P>
<P>
"Elders are the guide for the young generation. The experience
of the elders and the enterprise of the youth can ensure progress
of the society," the president said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the introduction of allowances for the elders,
Hasina said over 400,000 elders in the country are given monthly
allowances, and six "peace abodes" in the country's six divisional
headquarters are being constructed for providing food and shelter
to the distressed elderly men and women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
