<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Marks 50th Founding Anniversary (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Some 500,000 elated armymen and
civilians held a grand military and civilian parade at the
Tian'anmen Square this morning to celebrate the 50th founding
anniversary of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
The parade featured 90 floats and 38 square formations of
people of various backgrounds, 42 formations of troops and latest
weaponry including tanks, armored vehicles, missiles and a fly-
over display of 132 warplanes.
</P>
<P>
China's top leader Jiang Zemin and other senior Chinese Party
and State leaders reviewed the 2-hour parade from the Tian'anmen
Rostrum where the late Chinese leader Mao Zedong proclaimed the
birth of new China on October 1, 1949.
</P>
<P>
At about 10:00, the celebrations began with a 50-gun salute,
followed by the playing of the national anthem by a 1,200-member
military band and the raising of the five-star national flag on
Tian'anmen Square.
</P>
<P>
To the strains of a military music piece played by the brass
band, Chairman Jiang Zemin of the Central Military Commission
started reviewing the troops in square formations which extend
about three kilometers. After that he delivered an important
speech on the Tian'anmen Rostrum.
</P>
<P>
From the mid-19th century to mid-20th century, the Chinese
people fought bloody battles for 100 years and finally won the
national independence and people's liberation, thus changing their
destiny once and for all, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"From the middle of this century to that of the next, the
Chinese people, with hard and enterprising work of 100 years, will
by and large bring about socialist modernization. The Chinese
nation will stand rock-firm in the family of nations," the Chinese
leader said.
</P>
<P>
"The complete reunification of the motherland and the
maintenance of its security are the very foundation for the great
rejuvenation of the Chinese nation and the unshakable will of all
the Chinese people," he stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Marks 50th Founding Anniversary (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A rumbling roar broke out on the square when one after another
square formations of troops of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army, armed police, local armed forces and militia marched past
the Tian'anmen Rostrum, followed by columns of tanks, infantry
fighting vehicles and self-propelled guns. After that was a fly-
over display, featuring 132 warplanes roaring over the sky.
</P>
<P>
Holding their breath, the celebration participants watched the
spectacular scene in silence and burst into thunderous applauses
from time to time. This military parade is claimed to have
displayed the latest and the most advanced weaponry of the country,
and long-range ground-to-ground missiles and aerial tanker also
made their debut in today's parade.
</P>
<P>
Teams of singing and dancing civilian paraders, accompanied by
various music pieces played the military band, marched past the
Tian'anmen Rostrum, holding high huge banners expressing their
support for the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Lines of colorful floats showing China's economic achievements
and social progress during the last five decades added to the
spectacle of the parade.
</P>
<P>
Workers from the State-owned enterprises led the formations of
paraders and shouted their support to continued reforms.
Representatives from non-public sectors, an "important component
of socialist market economy", also took part in the parade.
</P>
<P>
The common aspiration for an early reunification of the
motherland was highlighted in the parade. "The issue of Taiwan can
not be delayed indefinitely," the banner on the float featuring
Taiwan scenery drew enthusiastic applauses from the spectators.
</P>
<P>
At the rear of the parade, a float with a model of a manned
spacecraft glided past the square, expressing the idea that China
has entered a countdown for the take-off in the 21st century. The
children on the square formed a new background pattern of Chinese
characters at that moment, which reads: "peace, and development."
</P>
<P>
By noon, tens of thousands of colorful balloons and white
homing pigeons were released into the sky, and over 10,000
cheering children on the square surged toward the Golden Water
Bridge right below the Tian'anmen Rostrum, pushing the
celebrations to a climax. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Reviews Troops In Grand Military Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang, in a Chinese tunic suit, made the review of all 42
troops formations composed of the People's Liberation Army (PLA)
three services, armed police, army reserves and militia in a "
Hongqi" or red flag convertible limousine along the Chang'an
Boulevard east of the Tiananmen Square in downtown Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's review of the troops is part of the full-dress National
Day military parade, which involves 11,000 military personnel, in
17 ground phalanxes and 25 vehicles formations, and ten echelons
consisting of 132 warplanes.
</P>
<P>
The parade, the 13th since the PRC was founded in 1949, is the
grandest featuring advanced weapons and equipment and the highest
level of mechanization.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after 10 o'clock, President Jiang, also general
secretary of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and
chairman of the Central Military Commission, left the Tiananmen
Rostrum and boarded the black limousine. The vehicle passed the
Tiananmen gate and the Jinshui (Golden Water) Bridge and cane to a
stop at the Chang'an boulevard.
</P>
<P>
Li Xinliang, commander-in-chief of the military parade who is
waiting for Jiang in another black convertible limousine, saluted
Jiang and reported: "Comrade chairman, assembly of the reviewing
troops is completed, please review!" The vehicle carrying Jiang
heads eastwards. The whole procession stretches some three
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
On Jiang's left side is the majestic Forbidden City, with a
huge portrait of late Chairman Mao Zedong hanging in the center of
Tiananmen; on his right side stands a huge portrait of Dr. Sun Yat-
sen, the great revolutionary fore-runner, in front of the Monument
to the People's Heroes on the Tiananmen Square.
</P>
<P>
The first reviewed is a guard of honor of the PLA three
services in brand-new uniforms, which raised the national flag for
the first time in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region at
midnight of July 1, 1997, when Hong Kong returned to the embrace
of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Next are formations of cadets from the University of National
Defense and other military academies, the infantry, navymen,
paratroopers, women soldiers, special police of the armed police,
army reserves and militia.
</P>
<P>
While reviewing the ranks, Jiang saluted the troops many times,
greeting: "Hello, comrades!" The soldiers at attention respond: "
Hello, comrade chairman!" Jiang said: "You comrades are working
hard!" The soldiers replied: "We are serving the people!"
</P>
<P>
Jiang waved to the soldiers of the vehicles formations composed
of tanks, armored carriers, guns and missiles.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the procession are the four formations of
strategic missiles, including nuclear missiles.
</P>
<P>
China began researching and developing strategic nuclear
weapons in the 1950s and 1960s. Now its missile troops has
developed into a major force in defending the national sovereignty
and maintaining world peace.
</P>
<P>
Jiang returned to the Tiananmen Rostrum along the same route,
with the reviewing soldiers at attention. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
