<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Largest Coalmine In North Central Chinese Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The Lingxin coalmine, the
largest in Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region in north central China,
has gone into operation.
</P>
<P>
Its designed annual production capacity will reach 2.4 million
tons. Estimated coal deposits in the Lingwu mining area where the
mine is located are 27.3 billion tons, equal to the total of three
northeastern Chinese provinces.
</P>
<P>
A central plan calls for developing a number of coalmines with
a combined production capacity of 11.6 million tons annually in
the Lingwu area by early next century.
</P>
<P>
The Lingxin mine is the first step toward building a large,
modern energy base at Lingwu and an effort to help improve the
standard of living here, authorities say.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
