<HEADLINE> Urgent: Civilian Anniversary Parade Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The civilian parade celebrating
new China's 50th founding anniversary now begins to the music of "
Ode to the Motherland" in this Chinese capital of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
A total of 500,000 people, including local residents from all
walks of life, representatives of provinces, autonomous regions,
and municipalities, and representatives of Hong Kong, Macao and
Taiwan are participating in the parade.
</P>
<P>
Marching in front are three protocol formations featuring
respectively the national flag, the year of the birth of the
People's Republic of China, and the national emblem.
</P>
<P>
