<HEADLINE> Army Helicopters Echelon Fly Over Tiananmen Square </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Motors roaring, an echelon of
armed helicopters in camouflage typical of the army airmen unit
are flying over the Tiananmen Square at a low altitude of 250
meters.
</P>
<P>
The airmen unit, with armed helicopter as the main technical
equipment, is widely deemed an important power in the air force of
all countries. China's army air unit, established in 1986, is the
youngest arm in China.
</P>
<P>
The emergence of the army airmen unit signals the entrance of
the Chinese army into a whole new period featuring integration of
surface and air.
</P>
<P>
So far, the army airmen unit has developed into a high-tech air-
striking force of certain scale that possesses various types of
planes and has considerable combatting capabilities.
</P>
<P>
The helicopters are flying at such low altitude that the pilots
are visible. lieutenant army commander Ma Xiangsheng, a special-
class pilot in the first helicopter flying over the Tiananmen
Square, was the highest-ranking officer in the entire military
reviewed today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
