<HEADLINE> First Generation of Central Leadership Praised in Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Now a float is moving past the
Tian'anmen Rostrum to the strains of the song "There would be no
new China with the Communist Party" praising the immortal
contributions of the first generation of central leadership with
Mao Zedong at the core.
</P>
<P>
The following several floats recall how the Chinese Communist
Party led the Chinese people in fighting bloody battles to win the
national independence and the people's liberation, including the
well-known Long March in the 1930s, and the War of Resistance
Against Japan in 1937-45, and the war against the reactionary
Kuomintang troops between 1945 and 1949.
</P>
<P>
Since the founding of the People's Republic, China, under the
leadership of the first generation of leaders of the Party, China
provided ample food for the world's largest population, conducted
nuclear tests, launched man-made satellites, and built big oil
fields.
</P>
<P>
These achievements are illustrated with 10 floats in the first
part of the civilian parade.
</P>
<P>
Traditional lion and dragon dances are performed following the
end of the first part of the parade, symbolizing that China, the "
Oriental Lion", had waken up and the Chinese Nation started
striding forward. 
