<HEADLINE> Parade Shows China's Achievements in Reform, Opening up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- China's miracle created through
reform and opening up in the past 20 years is now shown in today's
military and civilian parade marking the 50th birthday of new
China.
</P>
<P>
It also shows that China is becoming a strong modernized
socialist country with burgeoning prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The parade highlights on a float a huge portrait of the late
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping, the architect of the reform and
opening up which began in 1979.
</P>
<P>
In the following formations are floats featuring slogans that
call for holding high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory and
pushing forward the building of socialism with Chinese
characteristics into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The parade shows the achievements in different industries
ranging from energy to electronics, telling of the fact that China
is catching up with or surpassing developed countries in many
areas.
</P>
<P>
The parade displays some huge models and sculptures, including
nuclear power stations, the Three Gorge Dam, satellites, highways
and modern residential quarters, showing that the people's life
quality has improved.
</P>
<P>
Tax collectors, bankers, workers, artists, Buddhists, the
handicapped and college students are singing and dancing past the
Tian'anmen Rostrum, expressing their support to the current
leadership and their determination to overcome any difficulties
ahead.
</P>
<P>
The parade also exhibits the country's progress in the
reunification of the motherland with three floats representing the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
