<HEADLINE> Special Paraders in National Day Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A float carrying a cartoon
couple is moving past the Tian'anmen Rostrum along with a
formation of 3,500 Beijing residents.
</P>
<P>
The float illustrates China's success in carrying out the
family planning policy. The policy helped China save a total of 7.
4 trillion yuan which would have been needed in raising children
in the past 20 years if the country did not have 300 million less
babies born during the period.
</P>
<P>
The formation is composed of 275 couples, young and old, and
128 three-member families, marching with a huge slogan "Reform and
Opening up". These couples and families represent those across the
country who have benefited a lot from the country's policy of
family planning.
</P>
<P>
The formation also includes senior Chinese citizens, youngsters,
teachers, the handicapped, government functionaries, shop
assistants and religious believers. They hold flowers, pigeons,
flags, windmills, and balloons among others in their hands.
