<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Air Echelon Embraces Airmen of All Three Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The huge contingent of more than 100 aircraft that constitute
the 10 air echelons for the military parade today involve airmen
from the army, navy and air force, a composition that has never
appeared in the history of National Day military parade.
</P>
<P>
The scale of the air review is the largest in the history of
China's military parade, ranging from bombers, fighters, ground-
attack aircraft, to strike fighters of the navy air unit and
helicopters of the army air unit.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese-made aerial refuel tank which makes debut today
attracts special attention. When a refuel tanker dragging a long
pipe flies over the square along with oil-receiving planes, no one
would cast suspicion over the marked improvement in long-range
combat capability of the Chinese air force.
</P>
<P>
Also unveiled is the "Fei Bao", or flying leopard which belongs
to the navy air unit. Despite a short flying performance during
the Aerospace Exposition last year, few have had the opportunity
to observe the aircraft, China's first generation of fighter-
bomber.
</P>
<P>
Made in China, the helicopter of the army air unit is the very
type used in the air unit of the People's Liberation Army
stationed in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
