<HEADLINE> Common Aspiration of Chinese People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Now approaching the Tian'anmen
Rostrum are three floats expressing the strong aspiration for a
peaceful reunification of the motherland of the entire Chinese
people.
</P>
<P>
On the three floats at the rear of the regional float group are
pictures of high-rises of Hong Kong, a countdown clock showing the
coming return of Macao to the motherland, and sculptures and
charts showing the natural scenery of Taiwan island.
</P>
<P>
The three floats express the complete success of the policy of
"one country, two systems" and the fact that Taiwan is an
inalienable part of China.
</P>
<P>
The floats, thus depicting a returned Hong Kong, a returning
Macao and the Taiwan Island expected to return to the motherland,
speak out the common aspiration of the 1.2-odd billion Chinese
people for an early reunification of the country.
</P>
<P>
The most conspicuous on the float of Macao is a count-down
clock, reminding people of the imminent return of Macao to the
embrace of the motherland after 400 years' Portuguese colonial
rule.
</P>
<P>
"The issue of Taiwan can not be put off indefinitely," says a
banner at the float representing Taiwan Island.  
</P>
