<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0274 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's GDP Grows 5.5 Percent in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The Indian economy has shown
signs of recovery with gross national product (GDP) growing by 5.5
percent in the first quarter (April-June) of the 1999-2000 fiscal
year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Central Statistical Organization, year-on-year
GDP growth in the first quarter (April-June 1998) of the previous
fiscal was 3.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The budget estimate for GDP growth for the current fiscal is
6.5 percent while the Department of Statistics has projected a
rate of 5.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The GDP growth was boosted mainly by an improved performance in
the manufacturing and services sectors as opposed to the last
quarter of 1998-1999 when it was fueled by agriculture.
</P>
<P>
While manufacturing showed an increase of 6.2 percent over the
corresponding period last year, financing, insurance, real estate
and business services grew at 7.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Community, social and personal services also grew at 7.8
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
