<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exhibit on Deng Xiaoping's Hometown Attracts Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, October 1 (Xinhua) -- More than 100,000 people have
visited an exhibit in Chengdu, capital city of Sichuan, showing
the changes in Guang'an, also in Sichuan, which is the hometown of
the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
The 10-day show was scheduled to close September 27, but had to
be extended to October 7 because of the number of visitors.
</P>
<P>
Many queue to take pictures in front of the miniature of Deng's
old home, others leave messages in the visitor's book to thank the
late leader for bringing improved lives.
</P>
<P>
This demonstrates the Chinese continued admiration for Deng
Xiaoping, according to Li Chengxuan, deputy secretary of the Guang
'an Party Committee.
</P>
<P>
Deng was born in 1905, and left home at the age of 15 for
France in a work-study program in 1919.
</P>
<P>
The exhibit shows the changes in Guang'an over the past 50
years. In 1998, the city's had a GDP of 11.7 billion yuan (1.4
billion U.S. dollars) and industrial output worth 7.3 billion yuan,
29 times and 330 times the 1949 figures, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
