<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's National Day Celebrations Begin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- China's grandest National Day
celebrations in history now begin at 10:00 at the Tian'anmen
Square area here in Beijing, the Chinese capital, Beijing
Municipal Party Committee secretary and member of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee Jia
Qinglin has announced.
</P>
<P>
Jia's announcement is followed by a 50-gun salute and a
national flag raising ceremony amid the strains of the Chinese
national anthem played by a 1,200-member military band.
</P>
<P>
Some 500,000 armymen and civilians from all walks of life of
the Chinese capital have converged onto the Tian'anmen Square,
Chang'an Avenue and nearby streets. China's most important
political activities are usually held here, including the grand
ceremony marking the founding of new China 50 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Top Chinese leader Jiang Zemin will review the square
formations of the People's Liberation Army and a grand civilian
parade will be held shortly.
</P>
<P>
The grand National Day celebrations are the second in 15 years
since China's reform and opening-up. The first was held in 1984.
</P>
</TEXT>
