<HEADLINE> Urgent: Grand Flag-Raising for PRC Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A grand flag-raising ceremony in
celebration of the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic of China (PRC) begins at the Tian'anmen Square
of Beijing at around 10:00 this morning.
</P>
<P>
Jia Qinglin, a member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee and secretary of the CPC
Beijing Municipal Committee, announced minutes earlier the start
of the anniversary celebrations on the Tian'anmen Rostrum.
</P>
<P>
Amid a 50-gun salute, a national flag guarding contingent
consisting of 200 armed police in olive green uniforms walk down
the platform of the Monument to the People's Heroes in the
southern part of the Tian'anmen Square, marching northerly on a 10-
meter-wide red carpet spread along the north-south axial line of
the square toward the national flag post.
</P>
<P>
A soldier presses the button to raise the flag to the top of a
30-meter pole.
</P>
<P>
Watching the ceremony are Chinese leaders on the Tian'anmen
Rostrum and tens of thousands of people at the square who sing the
national anthem.
</P>
<P>
The Tian'anmen Square is believed to be the largest city square
in the world. Fifty years ago, the founding ceremony of the
People's Republic of China was held at the square and the late
Chinese Chairman Mao Zedong announced the birth of New China. Mao
pressed the button to hoist the first national flag of New China.
</P>
</TEXT>
