<HEADLINE> Marine Corps Debuts In Military Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Founded in 1980, the crack corps is one of the five major
services of the Chinese navy and is composed of infantry,
artillery force, armored units, engineering corps, anti-chemical
corps, signal force, anti-tank missile unit, and amphibious scouts
unit.
</P>
<P>
With its multiple fighting techniques, the marine corps has
gained the name of "tiger on the land, dragon in the sea, hawk in
the air."
</P>
<P>
The corps has taken part in several of China's important
military maneuvers, and won acclaims in 26 military performances
staged for Chinese leaders, foreign heads of state and foreign
military attaches in China.
</P>
<P>
The crown 352 soldiers in the square formation have been
selected from the marine corps. They did a job in their rescue
work in last summer's flooding along the Yangtze River and won
praises from the PLA headquarters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
