<HEADLINE> EDS-China-Parade-Reserves (18) Army Reserves Appear In Military Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA) reserves, a new type of backup force to the regular
army, make its debut at today's National Day military parade.
</P>
<P>
The square formation of army reserves, marching in parade step
past the Tiananmen Rostrum, consists of government officials,
workers and farmers, as well as private enterprise owners.
</P>
<P>
The reservists wear green uniforms resembling those of the army.
What distinguishes them from the army is the special symbols on
their arms.
</P>
<P>
The members of the formation come from Party and government
organizations, factories and enterprises, towns and villages in
three counties of Beijing City.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1983, the reserves is a force which can be quickly
turned into an army when a war breaks out. 
