<HEADLINE> Twin Sisters Heading Women Soldiers' Formation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the head of the formation are twin sisters. They are the
first twin sisters appearing in the same reviewed troops.
</P>
<P>
Although the twin are only 22 years old, Zhang Weiwei, 1.68
meters tall, and Zhang Lili, 1.69 meters tall, have served in the
army for nine years. Both of them are studying in the Baiqiu'en
Military Medical Academy.
</P>
<P>
Like the twins, all the women soldiers in the formation are
from the academy, including more than 30 women from such ethnic
groups as the Miao, Bai, Hui, Man, Tujia, Korean, and Mongolian.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 ethnic minority groups in China boast of their own
female PLA officers. China has the largest number of women
soldiers in the world, who are playing active roles in such
military fields as medicare, telecommunications, art, education,
press, theoretical research, and command.
</P>
<P>
The air force has trained six generations of women pilots, and
the naval fleets now have female sailors. 
</P>
