<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Military Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The origin of the military parade -- a centuries-old ceremony
in China and many other countries -- can be traced back to ancient
China, ancient Egypt, Persia and Rome. Over 4,000 years ago, Yu,
chief of a Chinese tribe in northern China, hosted a gathering in
central China of tribes from southern China, during which soldiers
danced to music and songs to welcome the guests. This is the
earliest recorded military parade.
</P>
<P>
Beginning in the 18th century, lavish military processionals
became popular in western Europe. Now, the events are held to
honor major festivals and large-scale military maneuvers.
</P>
<P>
The PRC has conducted 13 National Day military parades since
its founding in 1949. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
