<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reviewing Troops Ready For Grand Military Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
They are awaiting the start of a full-dress military parade,
billed as the grandest in China, to celebrate the 50th anniversary
of the People's Republic of China (PRC).
</P>
<P>
This year's military parade is the 13th since 1949, when the
PRC was founded, and the last one was held in 1984. The columns
are composed of more than 10,000 soldiers and over 400 vehicles of
various kinds, from the field, navy and air forces of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army as well as the armed police, army
reserves, and militia units. The soldiers wear brand-new uniforms
against a backdrop of camouflaged equipment like tanks and guns.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, awaiting the military parade at airports around
Beijing are ten flying squads, consisting of more than 100
warplanes. The ten echelons of warplanes are to fly over the
Tiananmen square during the military parade.
</P>
<P>
This year's military parade will display advanced weapons and
equipment made in China and feature the highest level of
mechanization. Some ninety percent of the arms and vehicles are
developed and manufactured in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
