<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A 87-km-long expressway linking
the cities of Qujing and Luliang in southwest China's Yunnan
province opened to traffic recently.
</P>
<P>
With four two-way lanes and a speed limit of 80-100 kmh,
construction on the expressway began in 1996 and cost some 930
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The new expressway, one of the key projects in the province's
Ninth Five-Year Plan Period (1996-2000), will facilitate the
economic development of the northeastern area of Yunnan, said one
transportation official.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the expressway has lengthened the
provincial expressway system to 373 km, and this length is
expected to reach more than 500 km next year.  
</P>
