<P>
King Birendra said he had visited China several times and the
visits "afforded me the opportunity to acquire firsthand knowledge
on the remarkable progress China has made in the economic and
social sectors."
</P>
<P>
He first visited China 11 years after diplomatic relations were
established between Nepal and China in 1955. Since then, besides
paying state visits in 1973 and 1993 and an official visit in 1987,
he has been to China on several other occasions.
</P>
<P>
The king, who has visited Tibet three times, said he is also
deeply impressed by the social and economic progress and
achievements in the Tibetan Autonomous Region of China.
</P>
<P>
"During my visits in 1976, 1982 and 1996, I have seen the
impressive economic and social transformation made by Tibet," he
said.
</P>
<P>
King Birendra expressed his satisfaction with the cordial and
friendly relations between Nepal and China. He said that China has
remained an invaluable partner in Nepal's development endeavors.
</P>
<P>
"As close neighbors, the traditional bonds of friendship
existing between our two countries are based on mutual trust,
respect, goodwill and understanding of each other's aspirations,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The king said Nepal attaches great importance to its relations
with China, as "the constant nurturing of our bilateral relations
is essential in the changing world scenario to ensure that cordial
ties existing between Nepal and China are further consolidated" in
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He especially noted the economic and social contacts between
Nepal and Tibet, which are connected by the same mountains and
rivers.
</P>
<P>
"We feel Tibet's economic progress can supplement Nepal's
efforts at economic development," said the king. "There is scope
for further cooperation in various fields such as trade, tourism
and investment."
</P>
<P>
King Birendra conveyed his congratulations to the leaders,
government and people of China on the occasion of the 50th
anniversary of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
"The Nepalese people join me in wishing the Chinese people
continued happiness, peace and prosperity," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
