<HEADLINE> China to Hold National Day Celebrations This Morning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- China is to hold a grand
ceremony this morning to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the
founding of new China at the Tian'anmen Square in its capital of
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The celebrations are scheduled at 10:00 amidst a 50-gun salute
with a national flag-raising ceremony and the playing of the
national anthem by a 1,200-member military band.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leader Jiang Zemin will review military troops and
deliver an important speech.
</P>
<P>
The military parade is expected to start at 10:30 with the
participation of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, armed
police, army reserves and militia.
</P>
<P>
There will be 25 formations of the country's latest weapons,
including tanks, armored-vehicles, artillery and missiles.
</P>
<P>
At about 11:00, dozens of jet-fighters, bombers and helicopters
will fly over the Tian'anmen Square.
</P>
<P>
This will be followed by the civilian parade consisting of 38
formations ten minutes later, which will be in three parts: the
founding of the People's Republic, reform and opening-up, and
march into the coming century.
</P>
<P>
A total of 500,000 people will take part in the celebrations,
which are expected to last about two hours.  
</P>
</TEXT>
