<HEADLINE> 500,000 People Gathered at Tian'anmen Square for Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- About 500,000 people, including
armymen and civilians, are now gathered at the Tian'anmen Square
and adjacent streets to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the
People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Divided into some 100 square formations, they are waiting for
the start of the celebrations at 10:00 o'clock. Among them are jet
fighter pilots, marine soldiers, workers, college students,
youngsters, handicapped people and young pioneers.
</P>
<P>
In the waiting formations are the country's latest advanced
tanks, armored vehicles, missiles, some 90 colorful floats
illustrating China's remarkable achievement over the past five
decades, and huge portraits of the late Chinese leaders Mao Zedong
and Deng Xiaoping, and the present Chinese top leader Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Some 100,000 primary and middle school students will form a
background setting with two Chinese characters "Guo Qing" (
National Day) in the square, facing the Tian'anmen Rostrum.
</P>
<P>
At the square are also a 1,200-member military band and 50,000
homing pigeons. 
</P>
