<HEADLINE> Tian'anmen Square Ready for National Day Celebrations (RECAST) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Tian'anmen Square, the world's
largest urban square, looks even more magnificent and solemn today
as it awaits the grand celebrations marking the 50th anniversary
of the People's Republic of China (PRC).
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of potted flowers have turned the square into
a mammoth garden in the center of the Chinese capital. Meanwhile,
the whole city is decorated with millions of potted flowers. The
national flags can be seen all over the city.
</P>
<P>
Some 500,000 people, including servicemen and civilians, are
gathered at the square and its adjacent streets, waiting for the
exciting moment.
</P>
<P>
As always, the Tian'anmen Rostrum is eye-catching with eight
large-size red lanterns and a glittering national emblem in the
middle. A huge portrait of the late Chairman Mao Zedong hangs over
the main gate of the rostrum.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the two reviewing stands on both sides of the
rostrum, temporary visitors' stands have been set up.
</P>
<P>
High above the square, 34 lantern-like balloons, five to seven
meters in diameter, and two huge floral-basket-shaped balloons are
floating in the air, while colorful banners are flying on
surrounding buildings.
</P>
<P>
A large portrait of Dr. Sun Yat-sen, forerunner of the Chinese
revolution, has been erected right in front of the Monument to
People's Heroes, with one slogan standing at each side of the
portrait.
</P>
<P>
One slogan reads, "Celebrate the 50th Anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic of China." The other reads, "
Hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory and march
toward the new century."
</P>
<P>
Red carpets have been spread on the grounds between the
monument and the pole of the National Flag, and between the Golden-
Water Bridge in front of the rostrum, and the main gate of rostrum.
</P>
<P>
A countdown board in front of the Museum of the Chinese
Revolution indicates that the long-awaited resumption of the
exercise of sovereignty over Macao by China on December 20, 1999,
is merely 80 days away. 
</P>
</TEXT>
