<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures About Coming National Day civilian Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A total of 500,000 armymen and
civilians will take part in the coming military and civilian
parade this morning in the celebrations of the 50th anniversary of
the founding of the People's Republic of China (PRC).
</P>
<P>
Following are facts and figures about the civilian parade:
</P>
<P>
The parade is composed of 38 separate square formations along
with 90 floats.
</P>
<P>
The parade consists of protocol teams and theme teams.
</P>
<P>
Some 5,000 young people will perform in the protocol teams
which form three square formations.
</P>
<P>
The theme teams will feature "founding and construction", "
reform and glory" and "century and take-off" and will be ushered
in by huge portraits of Mao Zedong at the grand ceremony marking
the birth of new China, of Deng Xiaoping at the Tian'anmen Rostrum,
and of Jiang Zemin delivering an important speech at the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The "founding and construction" part will be composed of five
square formations; the "reform and glory" part will have 21 square
formations; and "century and take-off" will have nine square
formations.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, 100,000 primary and middle school students at
the Tian'anmen Square will form different colorful patterns,
illustrating the parading formations.
</P>
<P>
The civilian parade will last for about 50 minutes. A total of
25,000 colorful balloons and 50,000 homing pigeons will be
released.
</P>
<P>
On the visitors' stands on both sides of Tian'anmen are
outstanding Chinese reformers, model workers, and other pace-
setters, representatives of Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan compatriots ,
overseas Chinese, as well as foreign friends from across the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
