<HEADLINE> Holders Parma Advance in UEFA Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Holders Parma came back from
their domestic dismal performances to lead the Italian charge into
the second round of the UEFA Cup on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
They were joined by regular league rivals Juventus, Bologna,
Roma and Udinese on an evening which produced rare surprises.
</P>
<P>
Without a win in serie A this season and with just four goals
from their four league matches, Parma overcame newcomers Kryvbas
Kryviy Rih 3-0 in a second leg clash in Ukraine to canter through
6-2 on aggregate.
</P>
<P>
France's Alain Boghossian opened the scoring for Parma with a
header in the 36th minute and Crespo made it 2-0 five minutes
before the break. Marco di Vaio, scorer of two goals in the first
leg, hit the final goal in the 67th.
</P>
<P>
Their Serie A rivals Juventus thrashed Omonia Nicosia of Cyprus
10-2 on aggregate after scoring five goals in each leg. Yugoslav
Darko Kovacevic made a rare start and seized a hat-trick in the
match in Palermo.
</P>
<P>
Bologna conceded the first goal and allowed the Russians a late
equaliser for a 2-2 tie, but Bologna still cruised through 5-2 on
aggregate.
</P>
<P>
Roma lost 1-0 to Vitoria Setubal in front of a crowd of 5,000
in Portugal but went through 7-1 on aggregate after the first leg
thrashing at the Olympic Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Former European champions Benfica, seemingly heading for an
early exit after losing 1-0 to Dinamo Bucharest in Portugal,
escaped with a goal in each half of their 2-0 second leg victory
in Romania.
</P>
<P>
Spain's Celta Vigo, who lost their first leg 3-2 away at
Switzerland's Lausanne, also survived with a 4-0 home win, thanks
to a hat-trick by South African Benni McCarthy.
</P>
<P>
Belgium's Club Bruges lost to Israel's Hapoel Haifa on away
goals after drawing 5-5 on aggregate while Denmark's Brondby were
also casualties, winning 4-3 on the night but losing 5-4 on
aggregate to Poland's Amica Wronki.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Helsingborg overcame Ukraine's Karpaty Lviv 4-2 on
penalties after having an 89th minute goal cancelled out by
Karpaty's 90th minute equaliser. 
</P>
</TEXT>
