<HEADLINE> Fifty Years Of Changes In Chinese Lives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese clothing, food, housing,
and travel have all seen great changes in the past 50 years,
Workers Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
Chinese clothes have gone from gray and blue uniforms to more
individual expressions and from keeping up with the Joneses and
copycat dressing and hiding brightly-colored shirts under a gray
exterior to choosing one's own clothes according to one's own
taste.
</P>
<P>
The food and methods of eating have gone from bran to
restaurants, from just having a meal of rice, noodles, or steamed
bread to frequently going out to restaurants of all kinds.
</P>
<P>
Housing has gone from newspaper decorations on the walls to
consulting professional design specialists. Chinese apartments and
houses used to have three generations of people crammed into a
narrow space, with walls decorated by paper cutouts. Now 68.3
percent of the families have their own apartments. They also have
televisions, refrigerators, telephones, and other appliances and
live in their own place.
</P>
<P>
Chinese have gone from always staying at home to traveling
around the country and even going abroad. It was very hard for
Chinese even to leave of their hometown in the '50s but more of
them now have the chance to travel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991001.0350 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Golden Jubilee Marked in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Ambassador to
Pakistan Lu Shulin Thursday gave a reception here, warmly
celebrating the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's Senate Chairman Wasim Sajjad, Speaker of National
Assembly Ellahi Bukhsh Soomro, Chief Justice of Pakistan's Supreme
Court Saiduzzaman Siddiqui attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
Also attending were Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff
Committee General Pervez Musharaff and other senior officials of
the Pakistani government and military.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the reception, Ambassador Lu briefed more than 800
guests on China's great achievements in the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
Lu reiterated that it is a "firm and unshakable" policy of
China to further consolidate its good-neighborly ties with
Pakistan and that "the Chinese government and people will,
together with the Pakistani government and people, exert
unremitting efforts in making our all-round cooperative
partnership even stronger in the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
In his toast, Sajjad said the past half century has been "a
golden period of extraordinary successes" for China. He spoke
highly of the achievements made by China in economic and other
fields.
</P>
<P>
"No doubt," he said, "China has a decisive role to play in the
coming century for the establishment of a multipolar world based
on justice and equity."
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his confidence that the Pak-China friendship
will play "a pivotal role" in bringing "a stable, better and more
prosperous future" for the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
