<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Parties Urged to Vote in General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The National Electoral
Board of Ethiopia Thursday called on all political parties to
participate in the coming national elections due to be held on May
14 next year.
</P>
<P>
The board said that it had finalized preparations to support
political parties interested in taking part in the elections, the
second of its kind since August 1995.
</P>
<P>
It was ready to accommodate opposition parties, both inside and
outside Ethiopia in accordance with the provisions of the
constitution and the proclamation pertaining to registration of
political parties, the board said.
</P>
<P>
"Now it is time for all opposition forces to register and get
into the election process," Aklilu Mekuria, election expert of the
board, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to local press, some 58 political parties have
announced that they will participate in the national and regional
elections.
</P>
<P>
Under Ethiopian constitution, parliament of the country
consists of the Council of People's Representatives and the
Council of the Federation.
</P>
<P>
The 550 members of the Council of People's Representatives, the
lower house in Ethiopia, are elected by direct vote for five yeas
terms.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Council of the Federation are elected by the
regional council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
