<HEADLINE> Paraguay Stops Sending 5 New Ambassadors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Paraguay's new
ambassadors in Germany, Brazil, Chile, Spain and the United
Nations remain in Asuncion due to lack of funds, according to
reports reaching here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry lately has been suffering from lack of
funds and its monetary situation is "terrible, very bad," said
Foreign Minister Jose Felix Fernandez Estigarribia.
</P>
<P>
According to Fernandez, the ministry at his charge expects a
budget increase of around 2.7 million U.S. dollars to fulfill
pending commitments.
</P>
<P>
"Until we can manage the situation, we are keeping former
representatives in their places. The international relations are
in no way affected," said an official source. 
</P>
</TEXT>
